time required: 15 minutes
---

olive oil
2 bunch spring onion
½ fresh chilli
1 bag snow peas
1 bunch mint
1 packet Japanese Dressing
1 tsp rice wine vinegar
½ tsp soy sauce
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet roasted peanuts

Thinly slice the spring onion and long red chilli (if using). Trim and thinly slice
the snow peas lengthways. Pick and thinly slice the mint leaves.

In a medium bowl, combine the Japanese dressing, rice wine vinegar, soy
sauce and a drizzle of olive oil.

Add the slaw mix, spring onion and snow peas to the dressing and toss
to combine.

Transfer the Asian snow pea slaw to a serving dish. Top with the roasted
peanuts, mint and chilli (if using).